---
import LibraryStyleLayout from "../../astro/layouts/LibraryStyleLayout.astro";
import "../../webComponents/sideTopTopNavigation/sideTopTopNavigation.css";
---

<LibraryStyleLayout>
  <script src="../../webComponents/sideTopTopNavigation/sideTopTopNavigation.js"
  ></script>
  <side-top-top-navigation>
    <div slot="primary-topbar">Primary Topbar</div>
    <div slot="secondary-topbar">Secondary Topbar</div>
    <div slot="sidebar">Sidebar content</div>
  </side-top-top-navigation>

  <main class="stt-navigation-main-content responsive-container">
    <h1>Side Top Top Navigation</h1>
    <p>
      This component provides fully responsive navigation bars using a Web
      Component:
    </p>

    <h2>Usage</h2>
    <p>
      To use this component, add the following code and insert your own HTML
      into the topbar's slots:
    </p>

    <pre>
      <code>
        &lt;side-top-top-navigation&gt;
          &lt;div slot=&quot;primary-topbar&quot;&gt;Primary Topbar&lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;div slot=&quot;secondary-topbar&quot;&gt;Secondary Topbar&lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;div slot=&quot;sidebar&quot;&gt;Sidebar content&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/side-top-top-navigation&gt;
      </code>
    </pre>

    <p><b>Info:</b> You need to add your own styles to the topbar content.</p>

    <p>
      The second thing you need is to adjust your website layout by adding the
      class <code>stt-navigation-main-content</code>:
    </p>

    <pre>
      <code>
        &lt;main class=&quot;stt-navigation-main-content responsive-container&quot;&gt;
          ...your content
        &lt;/main&gt;
      </code>
    </pre>

    <p>
      <b>Info:</b> As you can see, you can combine the layout class with the <code
        >responsive-container</code
      > class to improve page responsiveness.
    </p>
  </main>
</LibraryStyleLayout>
